  "handoff_packets": [
    {
      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"tdd_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: tdd_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nMake the supervisor PRODUCE agentic worker receipts by spawning workers, instead of only grading caller-supplied ones. The grade and enforcement path is already wired: run_dual_agent_workflow calls verify_dynamic_workflow_receipts / _evaluate_agentic_lead_policy at workflow_start and blocks before /lead runs. The supervisor-owned executor already exists in supervisor/agentic_workers.py: run_agentic_worker spawns a subprocess under .handoff/agentic-workers/<task>/<worker>/, captures stdout/stderr/transcript/output, and sha256-hashes them; run_agentic_worker_fanout pools them. The missing link is that no production code produces the receipts. Connect producer to existing grader. Scope: wire run_agentic_worker_fanout into the execution path for agentic_lead_policy allowed|required; /lead plans a machine-readable read-only worker roster, supervisor validates and spawns, /lead synthesizes worker outputs into typed dual_agent_outcome, Codex validates with P13/P14 and independent review. Enforce read-only workers by rejecting writable roster specs, enforce per-agent timeout and budget caps, and call cleanup_orphaned_agentic_workers for timed-out/dead workers. Confirm .handoff/agentic-workers receipts derive runtime_native and required runs can satisfy required_evidence_grade=runtime_native while lead-self/non-supervisor-path and docs/dual-agent transcript/output refs do not over-credit runtime-native worker evidence. Also make solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates gate-type-aware and add direct detached workflow job payload characterization coverage for all agentic policy fields. Non-goals: no eval harness, no native Claude TeamCreate fan-out, no default enablement, no gate-sequence weakening, no 4th reviewer registry, no raw MCP transport auto-reconnect.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\\n\\nCorrective context from the previous round:\\ncursor_review_failed: missing dual_agent_outcome block\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/agentic-lead-executor-wiring-20260531/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"606ddb18d8ebdbef8b070de1b832d8c0d21bead0f86e6270bd3dbc3fe60fa013\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/agentic-lead-executor-wiring-20260531/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"b0893b67697af89084fc1a44cbc4b13b7346e8ad50818a7fa7b2dc5e784bddf4\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/agentic-lead-executor-wiring-20260531/source